# shadcn/ui

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements. Do not introduce alternate component libraries (MUI, Chakra, raw unstyled primitives for standard controls, etc.).

## Project setup

shadcn is already configured. See [components.json](mdc:components.json) for style, aliases, and paths. UI components live under [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui/) and are imported via `@/components/ui/<name>`.

Shared utilities: [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) (`cn()` for class merging).

## When building UI

1. Prefer existing components from `@/components/ui` before creating custom markup.
2. Compose shadcn primitives rather than duplicating their styles.
3. If a shadcn component is missing, install it (see below) instead of hand-rolling a substitute.

## CLI commands

If shadcn is not initialized (no `components.json`), run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

To add a component that is not installed yet (example: button):

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the component name from the [shadcn docs](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components).

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — use installed shadcn components
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

// ❌ BAD — ad-hoc button when Button exists or can be added
<button className="rounded-md bg-primary px-4 py-2">Save</button>
```
